```man
.TH HSH 1 "Simple Shell" "Holberton School"
.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh
.RI [ command ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple shell program that executes commands read from standard input.
It behaves similarly to /bin/sh for basic command execution.

The shell works in both interactive and non-interactive modes.

.SH USAGE
Interactive mode:
.PP
$ ./hsh
($) /bin/ls
($) exit

Non-interactive mode:
.PP
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh

.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 on success. Errors are reported to standard error.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
Uses the current environment for command execution.

.SH AUTHORS
See AUTHORS file.

.SH SEE ALSO
sh(1)
